[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And the sons of Bela.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The names are wholly different in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 8:3-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The reason would seem to be that the names before us represent the chieftains and clans of Bela as they existed at a given epoch, viz., the time of David’s census. The list of 1 Chronicles 8 belongs to another period. Here, as elsewhere, it is evident enough that the chronicler has faithfully followed or rather transcribed his sources, without a thought of harmonising their apparent inconsistencies.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Heads of . . . fathers.—Rather, heads of their father-houses, i.e., chieftains.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Heads of",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": ". . .",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "fathers.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "heads of their",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "father-houses, i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " chieftains.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And were reckoned by their genealogies.—And their census was 22,034. This number represents the fighting strength of the Belaites,. who are here identified with their heads.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And were reckoned by their genealogies.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "And their census was",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
